full_text: Screened by NARA, 6/15/2023 Department of Homeland Security OMB No . 1615-0054; Expires 10/31/05 U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services Form N-445, Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony A# A046040013 WSC*001082160 Date November 24, 2004 APPLICANT COPY CASIMIRA ESCOBAR DE RAYMUNDO FOIA (b)(6) 37 You are hereby notified to appear for a Naturalization Oath Ceremony on: Friday, December 17 2004 at: US DISTRICT COURT CENTRAL DISTRICT 1201 SOUTH FIGUEROA STREET LOS ANGELES, CA 90012 LOS ANGELESCONVENTION CENTER, HALL, GATE NONE 1:00 PM Please report promptly at You must bring the following with you: This letter, WITH ALL THE QUESTIONS ON PAGE 2 ANSWERED. TYPE OR PRINT ANSWERS IN BLACK INK. Permanent Resident Card. Reentry Permit or Refugee Travel Document. Any Immigration documents you may have. If the naturalization application is on behalf of your child (children), bring your child (children). Other. Proper attire should be worn. If you cannot come to this ceremony, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, you will be sent another notice of ceremony at a later date. You must appear at an oath ceremony to complete the naturalization process. Form N-445 (Rev. 09/12/03)N
